    div(id="cvText", class="intro tile")
      p I started my search as a child by singing with my musical brothers but I gave it up for dancing
      p I tried different rhythms, first, tap-dance, then Spanish Flamenco, tango for a while and now I rejoice myself in the study of classical dancing
      p I was always fascinated by the customs and to play and recreate different situations
      p I began to study the career of fashion design and I designed and made clothes with crotchet neweedles
      p Soon I found myself working on my own,and participating in a contest for new designers called “ If I were Dali” at the Centro Cultural Borges
      p I also worked at a jewellery shop called Minima
      p And at last I met “for the second time” the great artist Celedonio Lohidoy. Celedonio is one of the best designers of Argentina and he selected me to join his team
      p With him I Learned to treat the pieces as truly works of art, attaching real importance to the finishing touches of each on of them
      p I decided to continue my path on my own and to start my company.
      p So I find myself developing my own artistic jewellery in which I try to exalt different sensations through different materials
      p Then I realized that knowing the designing techniques was not enough and that I should complete my training with a base of artistic knowledge
      p So I studied History of the Arts in the National Museum of Buenos Aires and afterwards I took lessons on plastic arts (specifically the study of the colour) at the atelier of the plastic artist Maika
      p I expanded my business to Europe.  I made an exhibition at a Gallery in Madrid. Also i sell my pieces at the Thyssen-Bornemisza Museum (Madrid). 
      p I studied coture millenary handmade hats classes (Madrid)
      p In Buenos Aires i sell at the National Museum of Decorative Art, Wussmann shop, Evita Museum and the Historical Museum of San Isidro: Dr. Horacio Beccar.
